## Running on SLURM

This template ships two complementary SLURM paths. Pick whichever fits.

### 1. Hydra multirun (composes with sweeps)

```bash
# One-time: install the cluster extra
uv sync --extra cluster

# Fill in your partition + account in configs/launcher/slurm.yaml first.
# Then fan out a seed sweep across SLURM:
python src/{{ package_name }}/train.py -m launcher=slurm seed=42,43,44,45,46

# Dry-run on a debug partition before committing to 24h jobs:
python src/{{ package_name }}/train.py -m launcher=slurm_debug trainer.max_epochs=2

# Compose with Optuna HP search:
python src/{{ package_name }}/train.py -m hparams_search=optuna launcher=slurm
```

Each Hydra config override becomes one SLURM job. Logs land in `multirun/<timestamp>/`.

### 2. Raw sbatch scripts (simpler, no Hydra submitit dep)

```bash
# Single GPU / multi-GPU on one node:
sbatch scripts/sbatch_train.sh experiment=example

# Multi-seed as a SLURM array job (one submission, N parallel runs):
sbatch scripts/sbatch_seeds.sh experiment=example
```

Both scripts assume `.venv/` exists on a shared filesystem. Create it on the login node with `uv sync --extra dev --extra cluster`.

### Preemption survival

The sbatch scripts use `--signal=B:USR1@90` — SIGUSR1 90s before walltime. Wire Lightning's `SLURMEnvironment(auto_requeue=True)` into your `Fabric(...)` call and your job checkpoints and requeues itself automatically.

### Notes

- **Partition & account:** edit `configs/launcher/slurm.yaml` or pass `hydra.launcher.partition=gpu hydra.launcher.account=xyz` on the CLI. Use `configs/local/` (gitignored) to keep machine-specific values out of git.
- **Optuna across jobs:** set `hydra.sweeper.storage: sqlite:///$PWD/optuna.db` on a shared filesystem so trials coordinate across nodes. Without shared storage, an N-trial sweep runs as N independent random searches.
- **Multi-node DDP:** outside the scope of these scripts. Use the `scontrol show hostnames` + `torchrun --rdzv-backend=c10d` pattern from the [PyTorch examples repo](https://github.com/pytorch/examples/tree/main/distributed/ddp-tutorial-series/slurm).
- **Container runtimes:** if your cluster has Pyxis/Enroot, add `--container-image=...` to `hydra.launcher.additional_parameters` in `slurm.yaml`.

## Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [Lightning Fabric](https://lightning.ai/docs/fabric/) | Multi-GPU, mixed precision — no hidden training loop |
| [Hydra](https://hydra.cc/) | Config management + CLI overrides |
| [TensorBoard](https://www.tensorflow.org/tensorboard) / [W&B](https://wandb.ai/) / [Aim](https://aimstack.io/) | Experiment tracking (switchable) |
| [jaxtyping](https://github.com/patrick-kidger/jaxtyping) + [beartype](https://github.com/beartype/beartype) | Runtime shape checking |
| [Ruff](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff) | Linting + formatting |
| [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) | Package management |

